  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The dataset titled \"Classification of research publications based on data from OpenAlex\" serves as a significant research output shared on Zenodo. With a total of 813 views and 73 downloads, the dataset showcases a growing interest in its content, reflecting active engagement from the research community.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">This dataset, authored by Nees Jan Van Eck from Leiden University and available on Zenodo, offers a valuable resource for scholars seeking to classify research publications utilizing OpenAlex data. The dataset's emergence in 2025 highlights its relevance in the ongoing discourse within the STEM fields, although it currently has no citations or online mentions across various platforms.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The interest in this dataset is evidenced by its 813 views and 73 downloads, suggesting that researchers and practitioners are initiating engagement with the dataset, potentially to inform their own research work or to explore classification methodologies. Such interest underscores the commitment to data accessibility and community reuse, essential principles in contemporary scientific research.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">While the dataset does not have accompanying social media or community discourse metrics, it stands as a foundational research output that contributes to the broader academic landscape. The absence of funding agencies indicates it was potentially developed without the support of institutional investment, yet the research's alignment with the key institution, Leiden University, embodies an academic endorsement of its value.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">As this dataset continues to garner attention, it will be pivotal to observe its impact on future research classifications and methods. The lack of downstream reuse metrics at this phase suggests an opportunity for further exploration and application in the academic community, which could enhance the dataset\u2019s visibility and utilization moving forward.</p>",
